<div id="review_231106050" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/231106050" />
    <a title="Judy" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3131238-judy"><img alt="Judy" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1358272075p2/3131238.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/231106050?book_show_action=true">Nov 04, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Judy" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Judy" href="/user/show/3131238-judy">Judy</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>


          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">lovers of historical fiction</span></div>

        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3131238-judy?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3131238-judy?shelf=uk">uk</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3131238-judy?shelf=2011-reads">2011-reads</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer231106050" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11060373761259064522"><a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/151723.The_Skystone__Camulod_Chronicles___1_' title='The Skystone (Camulod Chronicles, #1) by Jack Whyte' rel='nofollow noopener'>The Skystone</a> deposits the reader in pre-Arthurian Great Britain smack dab during the time of the waning Roman occupation. The account of Roman warfare, rule and order is impressive. In addition, I felt like an observer during the descriptions of iron-smelting and smith-ing. I liked this book for the historical angle and the story was good. Its probably getting a bigger knock than it should with my giving it 3 stars because it is following a couple of books that were exceptional. However, my best</span>
  <span id="freeText11060373761259064522" style="display:none"><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/151723.The_Skystone__Camulod_Chronicles___1_" title="The Skystone (Camulod Chronicles, #1) by Jack Whyte" rel="nofollow noopener">The Skystone</a> deposits the reader in pre-Arthurian Great Britain smack dab during the time of the waning Roman occupation. The account of Roman warfare, rule and order is impressive. In addition, I felt like an observer during the descriptions of iron-smelting and smith-ing. I liked this book for the historical angle and the story was good. Its probably getting a bigger knock than it should with my giving it 3 stars because it is following a couple of books that were exceptional. However, my best explanation for the mediocre rating is that the quality of writing reminds me of stirring up cake batter that is mostly smooth (like it should be) but contains a few lumps. Most of the book read well, but I felt that there were patches of <i>lumpiness</i>. My second peeve is the overuse of the insult, <i>whoreson</i> or <i>son of a whore</i>. I applaud the author for knowing these term even existed, but in the beginning of the book they were used much too frequently. My guess, these weren't the only way to verbally assault a man of this time period. It would have been nice if a few other barbaric words could have been slipped in in addition to this one. </span>
  <a data-text-id="11060373761259064522" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


